    "name": "The Diamonds",
    "profile": "The Diamonds are a Canadian vocal quartet that rose to prominence in the 1950s and early 1960s. Formed in 1953 the group has had a number of line-up changes and is still active.\r\n\r\nOriginal members: \r\nPhil Levitt (Baritone vocals, born July 9, 1935, died November 21, 2025)\r\nTed Kowalski (Tenor vocals, born May 16, 1931, died August 8, 2010)\r\nBill Reed (Bass vocals, born January 11, 1936, Toronto, Ontario, Canada, died October 22, 2004)\r\nDave Somerville (Lead vocals, born October 2, 1933, died July 14, 2015)\r\n\r\nIn 1958 Phil Levitt retired and was replaced by Michael Douglas, and, in the following year, two Californians, Evan Fisher and John Felton took over from Bill Reed and Ted Kowalski. ",
